## 📋 Pre-Commit Checklist

Before committing code, ensure:

- [ ] TypeScript compiles with no errors (`pnpm type-check`)
- [ ] Code follows naming conventions
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or API keys
- [ ] New services/hooks are exported from `packages/shared/src/index.ts`
- [ ] Components work on both web and mobile (if in `packages/ui`)
- [ ] Error handling is implemented for async operations
- [ ] Loading states are shown during data fetching
- [ ] Firebase security rules are updated if data structure changed

